(cpi, power_memory).explanation: Both CPI and memory power consumption are outcomes of the underlying processor design parameters rather than one directly causing the other;

(cpi, power).explanation: CPI and total power consumption are both performance and efficiency metrics that result from the same underlying architectural design decisions rather than having a direct causal relationship;

(cpi, power_pad).explanation: CPI and pad power consumption are independent outcomes of different aspects of processor design with no direct causal relationship between them;
